A vintage-style illustration of an abandoned lighthouse at dusk, its beam extinguished, standing on a rocky coastline. The lighthouse shows gentle signs of weathering with peeling paint in muted blues and whites. A single seabird perches on the railing of the observation deck. In the background, a warm amber sunset fades into deep purple twilight, with distant ships sailing away toward the horizon. The scene evokes a sense of quiet closure and transition, rendered in the soft, slightly faded tones of a 1950s travel poster with visible paper texture and subtle grain.
